The field of protoplanetary disks is currently being revolutionized by observational advances in near-infrared imaging (Subaru, NACO, and the upcoming Sphere and GPI instruments) and in (sub-)millimeter interferometry with ALMA. These observations of disks can provide images with comparable angular resolution (of the order of 0.03″\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
